<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SSL Certificate Report - {{ report_domain }}</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            padding: 20px;
            min-height: 100vh;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 30px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .header h1 {
            font-size: 2.5em;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .header p {
            font-size: 1.1em;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }
        .content {
            padding: 40px;
        }
        .info-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        .info-card {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .info-card h3 {
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.5px;
        }
        .info-card p {
            color: #555;
            font-size: 1.2em;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        .status {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 5px 15px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        .status.valid {
            background: #d4edda;
            color: #155724;
        }
        .status.expired {
            background: #f8d7da;
            color: #721c24;
        }
        .status.expiring-soon {
            background: #fff3cd;
            color: #856404;
        }
        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        th, td {
            padding: 15px;
            text-align: left;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #dee2e6;
        }
        th {
            background: #667eea;
            color: white;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            letter-spacing: 0.5px;
        }
        tr:hover {
            background: #f8f9fa;
        }
        .footer {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #666;
            font-size: 0.9em;
        }
        .timestamp {
            color: #999;
            font-style: italic;
        }
        code {
            background: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 2px 6px;
            border-radius: 3px;
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-size: 0.9em;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>🔒 SSL Certificate Report</h1>
            <p>Automated Certificate Lifecycle Management</p>
            <p class="timestamp">Generated: {{ report_timestamp }}</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="content">
            <div class="info-grid">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <h3>Hostname</h3>
                    <p>{{ cert_hostname }}</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <h3>Server IP Address</h3>
                    <p>{{ cert_ip_address }}</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <h3>Certificate Status</h3>
                    <p><span class="status {{ cert_status_class }}">{{ cert_status }}</span></p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <h3>Days Until Expiry</h3>
                    <p>{{ days_until_expiry }} days</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; color: #333;">📋 Certificate Details</h2>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Property</th>
                        <th>Value</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Common Name (CN)</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_common_name }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Subject Alternative Names</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_san }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Issuer</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_issuer }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Valid From</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_valid_from }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Valid Until</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_valid_until }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Serial Number</strong></td>
                        <td><code>{{ cert_serial }}</code></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Signature Algorithm</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_signature_algorithm }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Public Key Algorithm</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_public_key_algorithm }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Key Size</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_key_size }} bits</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Certificate Path</strong></td>
                        <td><code>{{ cert_file_path }}</code></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Private Key Path</strong></td>
                        <td><code>{{ key_file_path }}</code></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; color: #333;">🔐 Security Information</h2>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Security Aspect</th>
                        <th>Details</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Certificate Authority</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_ca_type }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Key Usage</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_key_usage }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Extended Key Usage</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ cert_extended_key_usage }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Managed By</strong></td>
                        <td>HashiCorp Vault PKI Engine (Automated)</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <div style="margin-top: 30px; padding: 20px; background: #e7f3ff; border-left: 4px solid #2196F3; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h3 style="color: #1976D2; margin-bottom: 10px;">ℹ️ About This Report</h3>
                <p style="color: #555; line-height: 1.6;">
                    This SSL certificate is automatically managed by HashiCorp Vault's PKI (Public Key Infrastructure) engine.
                    The certificate is monitored for expiration, and when it expires or nears expiration, a new certificate
                    is automatically requested from Vault, deployed to Nginx, and the web server is reloaded seamlessly without downtime.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="footer">
            <p>🤖 Automated SSL Certificate Management | Powered by Ansible, HashiCorp Vault & Nginx</p>
            <p style="margin-top: 5px;">Report Location: <code>/var/www/reports/ssl_report/index.html</code></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
